 See [[#get_drive|get_drive]] to convert returned index to the name of the drive.=== get_drive ===*  [[String GD|String]] '''get_drive''' '''(''' int idx ''')'''On Windows, returns the name of the drive (partition) passed as an argument (e.g. {{Span|C:}}). On other platforms, or if the requested drive does not existed, the method returns an empty String.=== get_drive_count ===*  int '''get_drive_count ( )'''On Windows, returns the number of drives (partitions) mounted on the current filesystem. On other platforms, the method returns 0.=== get_next ===*  [[String GD|String]] '''get_next ( )'''Returns the next element (file or directory) in the current directory (including {{Span|.}} and {{Span|..}}, unless {{Span|skip_navigational}} was given to [[#list_dir_begin|list_dir_begin]]).The name of the file or directory is returned (and not its full path). Once the stream has been fully processed, the method returns an empty String and closes the stream automatically (i.e. [[#list_dir_end|list_dir_end]] would not be mandatory in such a case).=== get_space_left ===*  int '''get_space_left ( )'''On UNIX desktop systems, returns the available space on the current directory's disk. On other platforms, this information is not available and the method returns 0 or -1.=== list_dir_begin ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''list_dir_begin''' '''(''' bool skip_navigational=false, bool skip_hidden=false ''')'''Initializes the stream used to list all files and directories using the [[#get_next|get_next]] function, closing the current opened stream if needed. Once the stream has been processed, it should typically be closed with [[#list_dir_end|list_dir_end]].If {{Span|skip_navigational}} is {{Span|true}}, {{Span|.}} and {{Span|..}} are filtered out.If {{Span|skip_hidden}} is {{Span|true}}, hidden files are filtered out.=== list_dir_end ===*  void '''list_dir_end ( )'''Closes the current stream opened with [[#list_dir_begin|list_dir_begin]] (whether it has been fully processed with [[#get_next|get_next]] or not does not matter).=== make_dir ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''make_dir''' '''(''' [[String GD|String]] path ''')'''Creates a directory. The argument can be relative to the current directory, or an absolute path. The target directory should be placed in an already existing directory (to create the full path recursively, see [[#make_dir_recursive|make_dir_recursive]]).Returns one of the [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] code constants ({{Span|OK}} on success).=== make_dir_recursive ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''make_dir_recursive''' '''(''' [[String GD|String]] path ''')'''Creates a target directory and all necessary intermediate directories in its path, by calling [[#make_dir|make_dir]] recursively. The argument can be relative to the current directory, or an absolute path.Returns one of the [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] code constants ({{Span|OK}} on success).=== open ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''open''' '''(''' [[String GD|String]] path ''')'''Opens an existing directory of the filesystem. The {{Span|path}} argument can be within the project tree ({{Span|res://folder}}), the user directory ({{Span|user://folder}}) or an absolute path of the user filesystem (e.g. {{Span|/tmp/folder}} or {{Span|C:\tmp\folder}}).Returns one of the [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] code constants ({{Span|OK}} on success).=== remove ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''remove''' '''(''' [[String GD|String]] path ''')'''Deletes the target file or an empty directory. The argument can be relative to the current directory, or an absolute path. If the target directory is not empty, the operation will fail.Returns one of the [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] code constants ({{Span|OK}} on success).=== rename ===*  [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] '''rename''' '''(''' [[String GD|String]] from, [[String GD|String]] to ''')'''Renames (move) the {{Span|from}} file to the {{Span|to}} destination. Both arguments should be paths to files, either relative or absolute. If the destination file exists and is not access-protected, it will be overwritten.Returns one of the [[@GlobalScope GD#Error|Error]] code constants ({{Span|OK}} on success).